title: Opening
description: Introduction to GDG and what the DevFest is.

title: Google for entrepreneurs – Learn how Google can propel your startup further
description: Our President gives you a walkthrough on how to handle your own startup, from idea formation to maintaining the startup, using Google for help every step along the way.

title: Firebase - Real-time platform for your  apps
description: What happens when you have an idea, an amazing idea, but here’s the catch: You don’t exactly know how to code it. Here’s where Firebase steps in to help out. It lets you focus on the front end while it handles the backend.

title: Android M
description: We’ll be teaching you how to make marshmallows and possible about the art of making s'mores over campfires. Well, not really. As much as we all love Marshmallows, this is more of a primer on the new version of Android.

title: Google AppEngine
description: If your servers can’t support the users, why not use Google’s hardware? Google app engine lets you build and run applications on Google’s infrastructure. We ask you to sit back as Shubhodeep and Ashwini teach you about it.

title: B Plan
description: Make your ideas bring you money

title: UI/UX
description: Get to know what knowledge in design you need to succeed in the professional world, by our UI/UX Expert Sauraj Babu.
